    "updated_at": "2016-08-10T17:37:56Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "My understanding of the fedora situation is that their package reviewers have decided that any library compiled from an outside repository (even ones from the same project) need to be packaged separately.  That is frankly stupid, and not at all our problem.  Taking the contents of that library/repo and importing them into OpenRA/OpenRA solves no practical problems and just makes our lives harder.\n"
  },
