    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@pchote Please note that the bundled library link that @rapgro links to is the list of reasons why Fedora prefers not to have bundled libraries. However, it is also important to note https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Bundled_Software_policy which states that bundling is no longer forbidden in Fedora and provides instruction on how to properly annotate the packages so that we know where bundling is occurring.\n"
  },
